"title": "4410: banquets",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4410: banquets",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Grand, celebratory meals consisting usually of rich food and flowing wine. Banquets usually accompanied weddings, religious festivals and other celebrations. Prophecies of the Messianic age refer to a banquet to which the righteous will be invited.</p>\n<h2>Characteristics of banquets</h2>\n<h3>They were usually held in a hall</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:4\">SNG 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:8\">EST 7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:10\">DAN 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Honoured guests were given special places</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:7-Luke14:11\">LUK 14:7–14:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:6-Prov25:7\">PRO 25:6–25:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:6\">MAT 23:6</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:39\">MRK 12:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:46\">LUK 20:46</a></p>\n<h3>Guests reclined on couches</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:6\">EST 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:7\">MAT 26:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:36\">LUK 7:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:2\">JHN 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Invitations were sent out</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:17\">LUK 14:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:3\">MAT 22:3</a></p>\n<h2>Occasions for holding banquets</h2>\n<h3>To celebrate weddings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:2\">MAT 22:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:21-Gen29:22\">GEN 29:21–29:22</a> <em>a feast celebrates Jacob's wedding</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:10\">JDG 14:10</a> <em>Samson gives a wedding feast</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:18\">EST 2:18</a> <em>Xerxes celebrates Esther's choice as queen with a banquet</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:10\">MAT 25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:36\">LUK 12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:8-John2:9\">JHN 2:8–2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:9\">REV 19:9</a> <em>the marriage supper of the Lamb</em></p>\n<h3>To celebrate birthdays</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:20\">GEN 40:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:21\">MRK 6:21</a></p>\n<h3>To celebrate other events</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:8\">GEN 21:8</a> <em>Abraham celebrates Isaac's weaning.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:17\">EST 8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:17-Esth9:19\">EST 9:17–9:19</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:23\">LUK 15:23</a> <em>The father celebrates the prodigal son's return.</em></p>\n<h3>Religious celebrations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:29\">PSA 22:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:21-2Chr30:22\">2CH 30:21–30:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:13\">2CH 35:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:6\">ZEC 7:6</a></p>\n<h2>Activities at banquets</h2>\n<h3>Good food and drink</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:6\">ISA 25:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:4\">JOB 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:6\">ZEC 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:4\">MAT 22:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:23\">LUK 15:23</a></p>\n<h3>Drunkenness and revelry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:36\">1SA 25:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:7-Esth1:8\">EST 1:7–1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:10\">EST 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:19\">ECC 10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:39\">JER 51:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:3-Dan5:4\">DAN 5:3–5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Music and dancing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:12\">ISA 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:6\">MAT 14:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:22\">MRK 6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:25\">LUK 15:25</a></p>\n<h2>Further examples of banquets</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:30\">GEN 26:30</a> <em>Isaac holds a feast for Abimelech</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:34\">GEN 43:34</a> <em>Joseph feasts with his brothers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:20\">2SA 3:20</a> <em>David holds a feast for Abner</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:15\">1KI 3:15</a> <em>Solomon gives a feast for all his court.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:3\">EST 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:5\">EST 1:5</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:9\">EST 1:9</a> <em>Queen Vashti holds a banquet for the women of the palace.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:4-Esth5:5\">EST 5:4–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:8\">EST 5:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:1-Dan5:2\">DAN 5:1–5:2</a> <em>Belshazzar has a banquet for 1,000 nobles</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10\">MAT 9:10</a> <em>Levi holds a banquet for Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:1\">LUK 14:1</a> <em>Jesus Christ is the guest of a leading Pharisee.</em></p>\n<h2>An invitation to a banquet seen as a sign of God's grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:12-Luke14:14\">LUK 14:12–14:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:23\">2KI 6:23</a> <em>The king of Israel prepares a banquet for captured Aramean troops</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:8-Matt22:10\">MAT 22:8–22:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:21-Luke14:23\">LUK 14:21–14:23</a></p>\n<h2>The Messianic banquet</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11\">MAT 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:29\">LUK 13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:15\">LUK 14:15</a></p>",
